  + [purpose] is measure finite Lambda phasor contribution layers near selected t-axis reference labels
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, RH evidence, zero certification, critical-line authority, primary zero detection, or special-prime hunting
  + [proof_status] is finite_lambda_phasor_reference_contribution_not_rh_evidence

& [MeasuredObject] is finite_lambda_contribution_accounting
  + [series] is E_{sigma,N,W}(t) = sum over prime powers q <= N of Lambda(q) W_N(q) q^(-sigma) exp(-i t log(q))
  + [term_contribution] is Lambda(q) W_N(q) q^(-sigma) exp(-i t log(q))
  + [layer_set] is prime_terms, higher_prime_power_terms, low_q_terms, high_q_terms, and exponent layers
  + [reference_labels] are first_zero_ordinate_reference, second_zero_ordinate_reference, and third_zero_ordinate_reference as labels only
  + [offset_policy] is centered_offsets around each reference label, including 0 and small symmetric offsets
  + [comparison_unit] is contribution share, complex vector angle, magnitude, real part, imaginary part, and finite residual when sigma > 1
  + [default_sigmas] are 1.5 and 1.05
  + [default_prime_power_bounds] are 100 and 500
  + [default_windows] are hard and fejer

  = must: include prime powers, not only primes
  = must: report exact input sigma, bound, window, reference label, reference t, sampled t, and offset
  = must: report prime versus higher-prime-power contribution separation
  = must: report top term contributors by amplitude and by projection onto the total phasor direction
  = must: compare to -zeta_prime(s)/zeta(s) only for sigma > 1
  = must: keep reference labels distinct from zero certification
  - never: interpret local contribution alignment as RH proof, disproof, zero certification, critical-line authority, or identity fusion

& [ImplementationPlan] is bounded
  + [step_1] is reuse rh_math.lambda_oscilloscope term formulas where possible
  + [step_2] is add a deterministic CLI script if existing term rows need aggregation
  + [step_3] is emit JSON trace into analysis\zero_behavior
  + [step_4] is record a finite analysis pass with contribution findings and restraint result
  + [step_5] is update CurrentFocalPoint with latest source, specification, trace, and analysis

& [AcceptanceCriteria] is bounded
  + [metadata_test] is trace proof_status finite_lambda_phasor_reference_contribution_not_rh_evidence
  + [reference_policy_test] is output contains first three reference labels as labels only
  + [layer_test] is output separates prime terms and higher-prime-power terms
  + [offset_test] is output contains centered offsets around each reference label
  + [boundary_test] is analysis preserves no-proof and no-zero-certification boundary

& [LambdaPhasorReferenceContributionSJS] is the specification justification trace
